      <head>Julius Hass</head>
      <div>
        <p>Austrian doctor and orthopedic surgeon, and the last noteworthy student of <ref cRef="entity-000537">Prof. Adolf Lorenz</ref>. Dr. Hass's most consequential publication came
          out in Vienna in 1934, the teaching manual <title level="m">Konservative und operative
            Orthop√§die</title> (Conservative and Operative Orthopedics).</p>
        <p>In 1918, Hass wanted to take lessons with Schenker. Since he could not read music,
          Schenker passed him on to <ref cRef="entity-000416">Marianne Kahn</ref>.</p>
      </div>
